[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1881-detroit-wolverines-season] Thompson bought most of the players from the defunct Cincinnati Reds franchise and formed the **Detroit Wolverines**, which joined the National League.
[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1881-detroit-wolverines-season] The team finished the season with a 41–43 record, good enough for fourth place in the NL race.
[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1882-detroit-wolverines-season] The **1882 Detroit Wolverines** finished the season with a 42–41 record, good for fifth place in the National League.
[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1882-detroit-wolverines-season] During the season, Detroit owner William G.
[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1882-detroit-wolverines-season] Thompson had a private investigator look into umpire Richard Higham, after suspicions of matchfixing, which resulted in Higham becoming the only umpire to be banned in MLB history.
[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1883-detroit-wolverines-season] The **1883 Detroit Wolverines** finished the season with a 40–58 record, good for seventh place in the National League.
[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1884-detroit-wolverines-season] The **1884 Detroit Wolverines** finished the season with a 28–84 record, finishing in last place in the National League.
[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1885-detroit-wolverines-season] The **1885 Detroit Wolverines** finished the season with a 41–67 record, finishing in sixth place in the National League.
[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1886-boston-beaneaters-season] The **1886 Boston Beaneaters season** was the 16th season of the franchise.
[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1886-detroit-wolverines-season] The **1886 Detroit Wolverines** had the best winning percentage of any major league baseball team to play in Detroit.
[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1886-detroit-wolverines-season] They compiled a record of 87–36 for a .707 winning percentage.
[src:1886-detroit-wolverines-season/1886-detroit-wolverines-season] Nevertheless, the Wolverines finished in second place, 2½ games behind the Chicago White Stockings.
